Wake up, Henry.

1161
01:13:19,144 --> 01:13:20,310
[GUN COCKS]

1162
01:13:25,818 --> 01:13:27,150
Karen....

1163
01:13:29,779 --> 01:13:31,488
HENRY:
What are you doing?

1164
01:13:32,198 --> 01:13:33,740
[KAREN SNIFFLES]

1165
01:13:34,118 --> 01:13:37,036
-Karen, are you crazy?
-I am crazy.

1166
01:13:38,329 --> 01:13:40,957
I'm crazy enough to kill both of you.

1167
01:13:43,836 --> 01:13:45,627
Karen, take it easy.

1168
01:13:49,132 --> 01:13:51,091
-Okay?
-Do you love her?

1169
01:13:52,677 --> 01:13:53,761
Do you?

1170
01:13:54,887 --> 01:13:56,972
-Do you?
-Karen...

1171
01:13:59,225 --> 01:14:01,644
I love you. You know I love you.

1172
01:14:02,854 --> 01:14:04,564
You don't.

1173
01:14:06,108 --> 01:14:07,817
No, you don't.

1174
01:14:08,444 --> 01:14:11,154
Please, be careful. Baby, don't.

1175
01:14:11,947 --> 01:14:15,240
KAREN: But still I couldn't hurt him.
How could I hurt him?

1176
01:14:15,408 --> 01:14:17,909
I couldn't even bring myself to leave him.

1177
01:14:18,078 --> 01:14:19,787
The truth was...

1178
01:14:19,954 --> 01:14:22,164
that no matter how bad I felt...

1179
01:14:22,875 --> 01:14:25,376
I was still very attracted to him.

1180
01:14:26,545 --> 01:14:28,880
Why should I give him to someone else?

1181
01:14:29,046 --> 01:14:30,881
Why should she win?

1182
01:14:34,595 --> 01:14:36,470
Just put it down.

1183
01:14:37,639 --> 01:14:40,056
You know I love you, don't you?

1184
01:14:40,309 --> 01:14:42,310
You're all I want, Karen.

1185
01:14:43,811 --> 01:14:46,021
Please put the gun down, Karen.

1186
01:14:46,899 --> 01:14:49,567
Baby, come on.

1187
01:14:52,570 --> 01:14:54,404
Shh.

1188
01:14:55,740 --> 01:14:57,908
Shh.

1189
01:15:03,498 --> 01:15:05,875
What are you, fucking crazy, Karen?

1190
01:15:07,252 --> 01:15:10,046
I got enough to worry about
getting whacked on the street!

1191
01:15:10,213 --> 01:15:13,882
I got to fucking come home for this?

1192
01:15:14,426 --> 01:15:16,426
I should fucking kill you!

1193
01:15:17,720 --> 01:15:19,555
How does it feel?

1194
01:15:20,599 --> 01:15:22,557
How does it feel, Karen?

1195
01:15:29,274 --> 01:15:30,440
[CRASH]

1196
01:15:30,609 --> 01:15:32,275
[GLASS BREAKS]

1197
01:15:33,612 --> 01:15:35,154
[DOOR SLAMS]

1198
01:15:37,615 --> 01:15:38,990
[CRYING]

1199
01:15:39,158 --> 01:15:41,118
I'm sorry!

1200
01:15:41,619 --> 01:15:43,162
[SCREAMING AND CRYING]

1201
01:15:48,126 --> 01:15:50,086
JANICE:
Hi, Jimmy! How are you?

1202
01:15:50,962 --> 01:15:53,965
JIMMY: Looking good.
JANICE: Thank you. Good to see you.

1203
01:15:54,131 --> 01:15:56,591
-Hi, Paulie!
-Hi, honey. How are you?

1204
01:15:56,760 --> 01:15:57,801
Good.

1205
01:15:57,970 --> 01:16:00,595
-Why don't you go get cigarettes, okay?
-Sure.

1206
01:16:01,472 --> 01:16:03,932
-Any of you need anything?
-I'm all right.

1207
01:16:04,309 --> 01:16:07,144
-Want anything to drink? A beer?
PAULIE: No.

1208
01:16:07,311 --> 01:16:09,896
-Chinese food?
PAULIE: No, come on, sit down.

1209
01:16:10,856 --> 01:16:12,358
[DOOR CLOSES]

1210
01:16:16,654 --> 01:16:20,408
Karen came to the house.
She's very upset.

1211
01:16:21,326 --> 01:16:22,743
You gotta straighten this thing out.

1212
01:16:22,911 --> 01:16:26,247
We got to have calm now. We don't know
what the hell she's gonna do.

1213
01:16:26,414 --> 01:16:28,498
She's getting all hysterical.
She gets very excited.

1214
01:16:28,667 --> 01:16:32,712
She's wild. And you got to take it easy.
You got children.

1215
01:16:33,671 --> 01:16:37,007
I'm not saying you gotta go back to her
this minute, but you gotta go back.

1216
01:16:37,175 --> 01:16:39,676
It's the only way.
You gotta keep up appearances.

1217
01:16:39,845 --> 01:16:42,262
JIMMY: The two of them
come over every day, commiserating.

1218
01:16:42,430 --> 01:16:44,431
I can't have it.

1219
01:16:45,600 --> 01:16:47,935
I can't do it, Henry.

1220
01:16:48,103 --> 01:16:50,938
Nobody says that you can't do
what you wanna do.

1221
01:16:51,105 --> 01:16:53,983
We all know that. I mean, this is what it is.

1222
01:16:54,150 --> 01:16:56,902
We know what it is.
You have to do the right thing.

1223
01:16:57,069 --> 01:16:59,154
You have to go home to the family,
you understand?

1224
01:16:59,323 --> 01:17:02,198
You got to go home, okay? Look at me.

1225
01:17:02,492 --> 01:17:04,702
You gotta go home. Smarten up.

1226
01:17:05,412 --> 01:17:06,953
-All right?
PAULIE: All right.

1227
01:17:07,122 --> 01:17:08,663
I'm gonna talk to Karen.

1228
01:17:08,832 --> 01:17:12,376
I'll straighten this out.
I know just what to say to her.

1229
01:17:12,877 --> 01:17:14,878
I'm gonna tell her you'll go back to her...

1230
01:17:15,046 --> 01:17:17,922
and it'll be just the way
it was when you were first married...

1231
01:17:18,091 --> 01:17:19,800
your romance, it's gonna be beautiful.

1232
01:17:19,967 --> 01:17:22,136
I know how to talk to her,
especially to her.

1233
01:17:22,304 --> 01:17:24,764
Jimmy and Tommy are going down
to Tampa this weekend...

1234
01:17:24,930 --> 01:17:26,056
to pick up something for me.

1235
01:17:26,224 --> 01:17:27,725
Instead, you go with Jimmy.

1236
01:17:27,893 --> 01:17:29,393
You come with me, we'll go down.

1237
01:17:29,560 --> 01:17:32,063
PAULIE: Have a good time.
Take some time for yourself. Relax.

1238
01:17:32,229 --> 01:17:34,064
Sit in the sun. Take a couple days off.

1239
01:17:34,231 --> 01:17:36,067
-We'll have a good time.
-Enjoy yourselves.

1240
01:17:36,234 --> 01:17:39,362
And when you come back,
you go back to Karen. Huh?

1241
01:17:39,529 --> 01:17:41,238
Please, there's no other way.

1242
01:17:41,405 --> 01:17:44,033
You're not gonna get a divorce.
We're not animali.

1243
01:17:44,201 --> 01:17:46,743
No divorce. She'll never divorce him.

1244
01:17:48,537 --> 01:17:51,414
She'll kill him, but she won't divorce him.

1245
01:17:55,753 --> 01:17:57,421
You gonna pay us?

1246
01:18:03,761 --> 01:18:06,805
-You gonna pay?
-Give us the fucking money!

1247
01:18:06,972 --> 01:18:09,391
I can't, I swear.

1248
01:18:10,935 --> 01:18:12,228
JIMMY:
Let's go.

1249
01:18:20,779 --> 01:18:23,447
JIMMY: We'll throw the bastard to the lions.
MAN: No!

1250
01:18:23,614 --> 01:18:26,324
What fucking lions?
I ain't going near any lions, Jimmy!

1251
01:18:26,493 --> 01:18:28,828
-Let's throw him over the moat.
HENRY: All right.

1252
01:18:28,994 --> 01:18:30,371
BOOKIE:
I'll get the money!

1253
01:18:30,538 --> 01:18:33,164
HENRY: They must really feed each other
to the lions down there...

1254
01:18:33,332 --> 01:18:35,083
because the guy gave the money right up.

1255
01:18:35,252 --> 01:18:36,918
I swear to Christ, I'll get the money.

1256
01:18:37,087 --> 01:18:39,212
We got to spend the rest of the weekend
at the track.

1257
01:18:39,547 --> 01:18:40,922
Yeah. They mean business.

1258
01:18:41,091 --> 01:18:43,717
Then, I couldn't believe what happened.

1259
01:18:44,136 --> 01:18:46,761
When we got home,
we were all over the newspaper.

1260
01:18:46,930 --> 01:18:50,015
At first, I didn't even know
why we got picked up.

1261
01:18:50,182 --> 01:18:52,309
Then I found out
that the guy we roughed up...

1262
01:18:52,476 --> 01:18:55,854
turned out to have a sister
working as a typist for the FBI.

1263
01:18:56,021 --> 01:18:58,899
Who could believe it?
Of all the fucking people.

1264
01:18:59,067 --> 01:19:02,278
She gave up everybody:
Jimmy, me, even her brother.

1265
01:19:03,654 --> 01:19:06,532
It took the jury six hours
to bring us in guilty.

1266
01:19:06,699 --> 01:19:09,952
The judge gave Jimmy and me 10 years
like he was giving away candy.

1267
01:19:10,119 --> 01:19:12,787
...ten years in a federal penitentiary.

1268
01:19:12,997 --> 01:19:15,957
You will now be turned over to
the United States Attorney General's Office.

1269
01:19:16,126 --> 01:19:17,792
[GAVEL BANGS]

1270
01:19:21,338 --> 01:19:22,965
MORRIE:
Toast, guys.

1271
01:19:23,132 --> 01:19:25,676
Good trip, good life, get out soon.

1272
01:19:25,844 --> 01:19:27,511
Good trip, sweetheart.

1273
01:19:27,679 --> 01:19:29,930
[GLASSES CLINKING, MEN CHATTERING]

1274
01:19:30,431 --> 01:19:32,515
We'll watch the home front.

1275
01:19:34,019 --> 01:19:36,479
Say hello to those blow-job hacks.

1276
01:19:37,521 --> 01:19:40,690
Yeah, motherfuck them
every chance you get.

1277
01:19:40,859 --> 01:19:42,193
[MEN LAUGHING]

1278
01:19:46,530 --> 01:19:49,073
I'll call you when I get a chance.

1279
01:20:01,462 --> 01:20:02,796
Now take me to jail.

1280
01:20:07,426 --> 01:20:10,220
HENRY:
In prison, dinner was always a big thing.

1281
01:20:10,555 --> 01:20:14,099
We had a pasta course,
and then we had a meat or a fish.

1282
01:20:14,643 --> 01:20:17,560
Paulie did the prep work.
He was doing a year for contempt...

1283
01:20:17,729 --> 01:20:20,064
and had this wonderful system
for doing the garlic.

1284
01:20:20,231 --> 01:20:23,234
He used a razor,
and he used to slice it so thin...

1285
01:20:23,400 --> 01:20:26,194
that it used to liquefy in the pan
with just a little oil.

1286
01:20:26,363 --> 01:20:28,322
It was a very good system.

1287
01:20:28,489 --> 01:20:30,990
Vinnie was in charge of the tomato sauce.

1288
01:20:31,158 --> 01:20:32,576
MAN:
Get the smell?

1289
01:20:32,743 --> 01:20:35,453
VINNIE:
Three kinds of meat in the meatballs:

1290
01:20:35,622 --> 01:20:37,664
veal, beef, and pork.

1291
01:20:38,041 --> 01:20:40,125
MAN:
Good, but you gotta have the pork.

1292
01:20:40,292 --> 01:20:41,836
That's the flavor.

1293
01:20:42,002 --> 01:20:45,463
HENRY: I felt he used too many onions,
but it was still a very good sauce.

1294
01:20:45,631 --> 01:20:48,425
Vinnie, don't put too many onions
in the sauce.

1295
01:20:48,592 --> 01:20:51,177
VINNIE:
I didn't put too much onions in, Paul.

1296
01:20:51,470 --> 01:20:53,264
Put three small onions, that's all I did.

1297
01:20:53,430 --> 01:20:55,975
MAN: Three onions? How many cans
of tomatoes you put in there?

1298
01:20:56,141 --> 01:20:58,894
VINNIE: I put two big cans.
MAN: You don't need three onions.

1299
01:20:59,061 --> 01:21:01,063
HENRY:
Johnny Dio did the meat.

1300
01:21:01,230 --> 01:21:03,815
We had no broiler,
so Johnny did everything in pans.

1301
01:21:03,984 --> 01:21:06,109
It used to smell up the joint
something awful...

1302
01:21:06,278 --> 01:21:09,238
and the hacks used to die,
but he still cooked a great steak.

1303
01:21:09,405 --> 01:21:11,948
-How do you like yours?
VINNIE: Medium rare.

1304
01:21:12,533 --> 01:21:14,659
Medium rare. An aristocrat.

1305
01:21:15,078 --> 01:21:18,831
HENRY: You know, when you think
of prison you get pictures in your mind...

1306
01:21:18,998 --> 01:21:22,626
of all those old movies
with rows of guys behind bars.

1307
01:21:22,793 --> 01:21:24,712
It wasn't like that for wiseguys.

1308
01:21:24,880 --> 01:21:27,547
It really wasn't that bad,
excepting that I missed Jimmy...

1309
01:21:27,716 --> 01:21:29,132
who was doing his time in Atlanta.

1310
01:21:29,301 --> 01:21:31,801
DIO: Give me two steaks
while you're in there, all right?

1311
01:21:33,137 --> 01:21:37,600
HENRY: Everyone else in the joint was doing
real time, mixed together, living like pigs.

1312
01:21:37,766 --> 01:21:40,769
But we lived alone. We owned the joint.

1313
01:21:40,936 --> 01:21:44,314
DIO: We batted them sons of bitches.
You couldn't recognize them.

1314
01:21:44,481 --> 01:21:45,815
Good, they deserved it.

1315
01:21:45,984 --> 01:21:49,278
HENRY: Even the hacks we couldn't bribe
would never rat on the guys we did.

1316
01:21:49,445 --> 01:21:51,404
DIO:
...had respect. People loved one another.

1317
01:21:51,573 --> 01:21:53,782
-They left their doors open.
-Sorry it took so long.

1318
01:21:53,949 --> 01:21:56,452
The skinny guard's getting to be
a real pain in the ass.

1319
01:21:56,619 --> 01:21:59,829
-We're gonna have to do something.
-I took care of him.

1320
01:21:59,997 --> 01:22:01,707
What'd you bring?

1321
01:22:01,875 --> 01:22:04,001
-Bread.
-Good. Fresh.

1322
01:22:04,168 --> 01:22:06,086
HENRY:
Vinnie, I got your peppers and onions.

1323
01:22:06,253 --> 01:22:08,421
Salami, prosciutto, a lot of cheese.

1324
01:22:08,590 --> 01:22:10,090
Come on, what else?

1325
01:22:10,257 --> 01:22:11,759
-Scotch.
PAULIE: Nice.

1326
01:22:12,761 --> 01:22:14,595
-Some red wine.
-Okay.

1327
01:22:14,930 --> 01:22:16,805
-Now we can eat.
-I got some white, too.

1328
01:22:16,972 --> 01:22:18,724
Give me the white, too. Beautiful.

1329
01:22:18,891 --> 01:22:21,894
Okay, boys, let's eat.
Come on, it's ready, Vinnie.

1330
01:22:22,645 --> 01:22:23,811
Some more bread.

1331
01:22:23,979 --> 01:22:26,398
Tomorrow we eat sandwiches.
You got to go on a diet, Vinnie.

1332
01:22:26,565 --> 01:22:28,650
-You must be kidding.
-Believe me.

1333
01:22:34,823 --> 01:22:37,743
[PAULIE LAUGHING]

1334
01:22:37,911 --> 01:22:39,328
What are you doing?

1335
01:22:44,667 --> 01:22:46,542
I'll take that.

1336
01:22:48,921 --> 01:22:51,381
-All right, I'll catch you guys later.
-Yeah.

1337
01:22:51,548 --> 01:22:53,884
You going for a walk in the park?

1338
01:22:55,386 --> 01:22:58,555
-Okay, I'll catch you next week. Thanks.
-Okay.

1339
01:23:01,393 --> 01:23:03,935
-Is there any more?
-No, that's it. Have a good weekend.

1340
01:23:04,104 --> 01:23:05,311
-Thanks.
-You too, Henry.

1341
01:23:05,646 --> 01:23:07,146
[DOOR BUZZES]

1342
01:23:08,190 --> 01:23:10,067
[CHATTERING]

1343
01:23:14,113 --> 01:23:15,154
MAN:
Mrs. Hill, come here.

1344
01:23:15,323 --> 01:23:16,489
Come on.

1345
01:23:19,868 --> 01:23:21,912
You girls stay right here.

1346
01:23:22,329 --> 01:23:25,582
-I want you to hold hands.
-Okay, go right up to the front.

1347
01:23:25,917 --> 01:23:27,835
-Let's go.
GUARD: How you doing?

1348
01:23:28,002 --> 01:23:30,212
KAREN: Good, how are you?
GUARD: Very well, thank you.

1349
01:23:42,475 --> 01:23:44,935
-What you talking about?
-I saw her name in the register.

1350
01:23:45,103 --> 01:23:47,270
HENRY: Jesus Christ.
KAREN: You want her to visit you?

1351
01:23:47,439 --> 01:23:51,108
Let her stay up all night crying
and writing letters to the parole board.

1352
01:23:51,275 --> 01:23:54,444
What am I doing here?
Where am I? I'm in jail.

1353
01:23:54,612 --> 01:23:56,738
I can't stop people
from coming to see me.

1354
01:23:56,905 --> 01:24:00,283
Good, let her sneak this stuff in
for you every week.

1355
01:24:00,452 --> 01:24:04,078
-Let her fight these bastards every week!
-Look what you're doing! Stop it!

1356
01:24:04,247 --> 01:24:05,663
[BABY CRYING]

1357
01:24:05,832 --> 01:24:07,791
-Shh.
KAREN: I'm sorry.

1358
01:24:08,292 --> 01:24:10,752
Let her sneak this shit in for you.

1359
01:24:11,796 --> 01:24:13,630
Will you stop it, Karen?

1360
01:24:14,090 --> 01:24:16,632
-Let her do it!
-Stop it!

1361
01:24:24,809 --> 01:24:28,103
KAREN:
Nobody's helping me. I'm all alone.

1362
01:24:29,146 --> 01:24:31,148
Belle and Morrie are broke.

1363
01:24:31,565 --> 01:24:34,777
I asked your friend Remo
for the money that he owes you.

1364
01:24:34,944 --> 01:24:36,319
You know what he told me?

1365
01:24:36,488 --> 01:24:40,073
He told me to take my kids down
to the police station and get on welfare.

1366
01:24:40,240 --> 01:24:42,201
It's gonna be okay.

1367
01:24:42,409 --> 01:24:46,497
Even Paulie, since he got out, I've never
seen him. I never see anybody anymore.

1368
01:24:46,663 --> 01:24:49,457
It's only you and me.
That's what happens when you go away.

1369
01:24:49,626 --> 01:24:53,628
I told you that we're on our own.
Forget everybody else. Forget Paulie.

1370
01:24:54,631 --> 01:24:58,634
As long as he's on parole,
he doesn't want anybody doing anything.

1371
01:25:01,095 --> 01:25:03,346
-I can't do it.
-Yes, you can. Listen to me.

1372
01:25:03,515 --> 01:25:06,100
All I need for you
is to keep bringing me the stuff.

1373
01:25:06,266 --> 01:25:08,851
I got a guy in here from Pittsburgh
who'll help me move it.

1374
01:25:09,020 --> 01:25:10,645
In a month we're gonna be fine.

1375
01:25:10,814 --> 01:25:13,148
-We won't need anybody.
-I'm afraid.

1376
01:25:13,315 --> 01:25:15,234
I'm afraid if Paulie finds out....

1377
01:25:15,400 --> 01:25:16,819
Don't worry about him.

1378
01:25:16,985 --> 01:25:20,530
He is not helping us out.
Is he putting any food on the table?

1379
01:25:21,698 --> 01:25:23,158
We've gotta help each other.

1380
01:25:23,326 --> 01:25:26,994
We've just gotta be really careful
while we do it.

1381
01:25:31,667 --> 01:25:33,877
I don't want to hear a word
about her anymore.

1382
01:25:34,045 --> 01:25:35,087
Never.

1383
01:26:00,654 --> 01:26:02,113
GIRLS:
Daddy!

1384
01:26:03,740 --> 01:26:05,993
JUDY: We missed you.
RUTH: Are you here to stay?

1385
01:26:06,161 --> 01:26:09,746
JUDY: Did you see our pictures?
I did the one with the house and rainbow.

1386
01:26:09,913 --> 01:26:11,331
RUTH:
I did the sun.

1387
01:26:11,498 --> 01:26:15,418
JUDY: My chorus concert is in two weeks.
Are you coming?

1388
01:26:16,253 --> 01:26:18,087
Do you like the house?

1389
01:26:19,381 --> 01:26:21,257
Karen, get packed.
We're moving out of here.

1390
01:26:21,426 --> 01:26:22,634
