It's over there, on the corner.

2062
02:11:01,270 --> 02:11:02,561
Right there.

2063
02:11:19,954 --> 02:11:22,122
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

2064
02:11:24,626 --> 02:11:26,210
MAN:
Shh, shh, shh.

2065
02:11:36,762 --> 02:11:38,890
No, go ahead. It's right in there.

2066
02:11:39,056 --> 02:11:41,141
KAREN:
No, Jimmy. I'm in a hurry!

2067
02:11:41,475 --> 02:11:44,270
My mom's watching the kids!
I got to get home!

2068
02:11:44,438 --> 02:11:45,979
I'll come back later!

2069
02:11:49,318 --> 02:11:50,818
[TIRES SCREECHING]

2070
02:12:08,420 --> 02:12:10,046
Karen. Karen!

2071
02:12:10,588 --> 02:12:12,088
[KAREN CRYING]

2072
02:12:14,551 --> 02:12:15,801
What happened?

2073
02:12:17,011 --> 02:12:18,470
KAREN:
Nothing.

2074
02:12:18,639 --> 02:12:20,514
-What happened?
-I just got scared.

2075
02:12:24,019 --> 02:12:25,185
Got the keys?

2076
02:12:26,939 --> 02:12:30,565
-What happened, Karen?
-I just got scared. It's okay.

2077
02:12:30,734 --> 02:12:32,359
-Are you all right?
-Yeah.

2078
02:12:39,242 --> 02:12:43,828
HENRY: If you're part of a crew, nobody
ever tells you they're going to kill you.

2079
02:12:44,372 --> 02:12:46,122
It doesn't happen that way.

2080
02:12:46,291 --> 02:12:49,710
There aren't any arguments
or curses like in the movies.

2081
02:12:49,877 --> 02:12:53,965
Your murderers come with smiles.
They come as your friends.

2082
02:12:54,131 --> 02:12:56,175
People who cared for you all your life.

2083
02:12:56,342 --> 02:13:00,720
They always seem to come when you're
weakest and most in need of their help.

2084
02:13:01,055 --> 02:13:04,307
So I met Jimmy in a crowded place
we both knew.

2085
02:13:04,685 --> 02:13:08,688
I got there 15 minutes early,
and Jimmy was already there.

2086
02:13:09,105 --> 02:13:13,525
He took the booth near the window
so he could see everyone who drove up.

2087
02:13:13,859 --> 02:13:16,237
He wanted to make sure I wasn't tailed.

2088
02:13:16,654 --> 02:13:19,532
He was jumpy. He hadn't touched a thing.

2089
02:13:20,574 --> 02:13:23,577
On the surface,
everything was supposed to be fine.

2090
02:13:23,744 --> 02:13:26,079
We were supposed to be discussing
my case.

2091
02:13:26,247 --> 02:13:31,210
But I had a feeling Jimmy was trying
to sense if I'd rat on him to save my neck.

2092
02:13:32,878 --> 02:13:36,590
I been telling you your whole life,
don't talk on the phone.

2093
02:13:36,800 --> 02:13:38,591
Now you understand?

2094
02:13:41,262 --> 02:13:44,597
It's going to be okay.
You got a good chance to beat the case.

2095
02:13:47,769 --> 02:13:52,064
You know that kid from the city
we were talking about? You know?

2096
02:13:54,650 --> 02:13:58,654
The kid turned out to be a rat. As soon as
he got pinched, he ratted on everybody.

2097
02:14:01,449 --> 02:14:03,367
I know where he is. He's hiding now.

2098
02:14:05,287 --> 02:14:06,619
Know what I'm saying?

2099
02:14:11,626 --> 02:14:14,795
Would you have a problem going
with Anthony to take care of that?

2100
02:14:15,380 --> 02:14:16,963
Mm-mm.

2101
02:14:17,882 --> 02:14:19,132
No, not at all.

2102
02:14:20,761 --> 02:14:22,344
That way they got nothing.

2103
02:14:31,188 --> 02:14:33,939
HENRY: Jimmy had never asked me
to whack somebody before.

2104
02:14:34,399 --> 02:14:38,069
But now he's asking me to go to Florida
and do a hit with Anthony.

2105
02:14:45,618 --> 02:14:48,953
That's when I knew I would never
have come back from Florida alive.

2106
02:15:03,345 --> 02:15:06,639
Whenever you move me,
I asked once and I'll tell you again...

2107
02:15:06,806 --> 02:15:08,640
I don't want to go any place cold.

2108
02:15:09,643 --> 02:15:11,810
You don't have a choice in that matter.

2109
02:15:12,186 --> 02:15:14,729
Come on. Whoever fucking controls it...

2110
02:15:15,524 --> 02:15:18,192
just no place cold. Do that for me.
I'm trying to--

2111
02:15:18,359 --> 02:15:20,069
He's bronchial, that's why.

2112
02:15:20,237 --> 02:15:22,947
If he's legitimately bronchial,
we'll consider that.

2113
02:15:23,114 --> 02:15:25,198
I'd like to go someplace not cold.

2114
02:15:25,367 --> 02:15:29,078
Can I ask you some questions?
What about my parents?

2115
02:15:30,037 --> 02:15:31,079
What about them?

2116
02:15:31,247 --> 02:15:33,832
Am I going to see them?
Am I going to talk to them?

2117
02:15:35,085 --> 02:15:37,293
Don't I have some kind of contact
with them?

2118
02:15:38,171 --> 02:15:39,212
No.

2119
02:15:40,340 --> 02:15:43,676
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
You mean to tell me that...

2120
02:15:44,051 --> 02:15:48,055
God forbid something happens to my
parents, they get sick, I can't see them?

2121
02:15:48,222 --> 02:15:51,225
Maybe something can be worked out
if they're sick...

2122
02:15:51,725 --> 02:15:53,894
if there's extraordinary circumstances--

2123
02:15:54,061 --> 02:15:56,896
I can't do this. I can't do this, Henry.

2124
02:15:58,024 --> 02:15:59,774
I can't leave my parents.

2125
02:16:01,027 --> 02:16:03,237
Excuse me, Karen, I told you before.

2126
02:16:04,488 --> 02:16:07,490
I'm not going to do this
unless you and the kids come with me.

2127
02:16:09,828 --> 02:16:11,494
I can't do it without you.

2128
02:16:11,912 --> 02:16:16,000
So, you do whatever, but...that's it.

2129
02:16:17,543 --> 02:16:20,003
-You need Henry, not me, right?
-That's right.

2130
02:16:20,421 --> 02:16:22,881
Frankly, I don't care
whether you go or not.

2131
02:16:23,216 --> 02:16:26,594
If it'll make him a better witness,
I'd like you to be with him.

2132
02:16:26,761 --> 02:16:28,345
They want Henry, not me.

2133
02:16:28,512 --> 02:16:31,599
Henry'll be in the protection program.
They can't get to him.

2134
02:16:32,516 --> 02:16:35,769
They can only get to him
by getting to you or your kids.

2135
02:16:35,936 --> 02:16:38,522
If he goes into the program,
you're in danger--

2136
02:16:38,690 --> 02:16:41,066
-I don't know anything.
-Don't give me...

2137
02:16:41,234 --> 02:16:42,735
the babe-in-the-woods routine.

2138
02:16:42,903 --> 02:16:47,281
I've listened to those wiretaps,
and I've heard you talk about cocaine.

2139
02:16:47,449 --> 02:16:50,783
Conversation after conversation
you talked to Henry on the phone.

2140
02:16:55,998 --> 02:16:58,083
It doesn't matter.
Whether he goes to jail...

2141
02:16:58,251 --> 02:17:01,545
or stays on the streets and beats the case,
he's a dead man.

2142
02:17:02,297 --> 02:17:04,005
He knows it and you know it.

2143
02:17:05,634 --> 02:17:07,343
What about the kids and school?

2144
02:17:07,510 --> 02:17:09,802
KAREN: Will they get left back?
I mean, what goes on?

2145
02:17:10,138 --> 02:17:12,556
TUDDY:
Go to Wall Street and get real crooks.

2146
02:17:12,724 --> 02:17:15,183
Whoever sold you those suits
had a sense of humor.

2147
02:17:15,352 --> 02:17:18,436
What it comes down to is
we're your only salvation.

2148
02:17:19,272 --> 02:17:22,691
We'll save your life and his life,
and we'll keep you out of jail.

2149
02:17:26,947 --> 02:17:29,573
This morning you told the jury
about your background.

2150
02:17:29,740 --> 02:17:31,575
HENRY:
It was easy for us to disappear.

2151
02:17:32,118 --> 02:17:34,245
My house
was in my mother-in-law's name.

2152
02:17:34,412 --> 02:17:36,371
My cars were registered to my wife.

2153
02:17:36,539 --> 02:17:40,000
My Social Security cards
and driver's licenses were phonies.

2154
02:17:40,167 --> 02:17:42,503
I never voted or paid taxes.

2155
02:17:43,087 --> 02:17:47,549
My birth certificate and arrest sheet was
all you'd ever have to know I was alive.

2156
02:17:47,717 --> 02:17:49,635
ATTORNEY:
Do you see him here in this courtroom?

2157
02:17:49,802 --> 02:17:50,843
Yes.

2158
02:17:51,012 --> 02:17:53,096
ATTORNEY:
Will you please point him out for the jury?

2159
02:17:55,683 --> 02:18:00,311
Let the record reflect that Mr. Hill
identified the defendant, James Conway.

2160
02:18:01,439 --> 02:18:04,524
Do you also know a man
named Paul Cicero?

2161
02:18:04,859 --> 02:18:06,860
-Do you see him in the courtroom?
-Yes.

2162
02:18:07,444 --> 02:18:09,362
ATTORNEY:
Can you point him out for the jury?

2163
02:18:11,324 --> 02:18:15,411
Let the record reflect that Mr. Hill
identified the defendant, Paul Cicero.

2164
02:18:16,745 --> 02:18:18,454
Your Honor, I have a document....

2165
02:18:18,622 --> 02:18:21,040
HENRY:
The hardest thing was leaving the life.

2166
02:18:21,876 --> 02:18:23,334
I still love the life.

2167
02:18:23,711 --> 02:18:25,629
We were treated like movie stars
with muscle.

2168
02:18:25,797 --> 02:18:28,048
We had it all, just for the asking.

2169
02:18:28,216 --> 02:18:31,551
Our wives, mothers, kids,
everybody rode along.

2170
02:18:31,886 --> 02:18:35,055
I had paper bags filled with jewelry
stashed in the kitchen.

2171
02:18:35,222 --> 02:18:37,474
I had a sugar bowl full of coke
next to the bed.

2172
02:18:37,641 --> 02:18:41,436
People call them rats because rats do
anything to survive. Isn't that right?

2173
02:18:41,603 --> 02:18:43,647
ATTORNEY: Objection!
JUDGE: Objection sustained.

2174
02:18:43,815 --> 02:18:47,400
-I know nothing about being a rat.
-You know everything about it.

2175
02:18:47,736 --> 02:18:49,444
ATTORNEY: Objection, Your Honor.
In view of the violence....

2176
02:18:49,611 --> 02:18:51,738
HENRY:
Anything I wanted was a phone call away.

2177
02:18:51,906 --> 02:18:55,325
Free cars. Keys to a dozen hideout flats
all over the city.

2178
02:18:55,493 --> 02:18:57,995
I'd bet $20,000, $30,000
over a weekend...

2179
02:18:58,163 --> 02:19:02,207
then blow the winnings in a week
or go to the sharks to pay the bookies.

2180
02:19:02,375 --> 02:19:03,709
It didn't matter.

2181
02:19:04,252 --> 02:19:09,130
It didn't mean anything. When I was broke
I would go out and rob some more.

2182
02:19:09,549 --> 02:19:10,924
We ran everything.

2183
02:19:11,468 --> 02:19:15,763
We paid off cops. We paid off lawyers.
We paid off judges.

2184
02:19:16,013 --> 02:19:19,433
Everybody had their hands out.
Everything was for the taking.

2185
02:19:21,560 --> 02:19:23,061
And now it's all over.

2186
02:19:23,979 --> 02:19:25,439
That's the hardest part.

2187
02:19:26,441 --> 02:19:28,066
Today everything is different.

2188
02:19:28,234 --> 02:19:32,404
There's no action.
I have to wait around like everyone else.

2189
02:19:32,781 --> 02:19:34,573
Can't even get decent food.

2190
02:19:35,325 --> 02:19:38,451
After I got here I ordered spaghetti
with marinara sauce...

2191
02:19:38,620 --> 02:19:40,453
and I got egg noodles and ketchup.

2192
02:19:41,289 --> 02:19:42,790
I'm an average nobody.

2193
02:19:44,166 --> 02:19:46,959
I get to live the rest of my life
like a schnook.

2194
02:25:11,494 --> 02:25:13,495

